6:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> uhm</span><hr size=1> so for someone new to the ranger class... what do I have to do for a trueshot bow, besides mastering fletching.... ?<br><br>Wyrd <p>Brandy.. a paladin's ambrosia.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uiznoz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iznoz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/01 2:27:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Trueshot worth it?</span><hr size=1> in steamfont is the place to start get all the microservos you can at least 12 (2 per attempt to make trueshot) this is the hardest part I think. If you make it past this part you only need to take a boat to free port get Trent wood (give a small lantern to a guy in a bar in west freeport) and then get on boat stop at sister isle and buy as many nuts as you can carry and be fast so you can get back on ship. go to kaladim give 1 nut and one water flask to tumpy for a tonic try to get about 24 tonics I know it sounds crazy but better to have extras then to run out of stuff. give two tonic to a guy in forge building (ironhot or something I forget name) for every two you get a dwarvish wire try to get about 12 (2 per attempt to make trueshot)  of these. ok now kill some spiderlings on your way to kelethin try to get about 6 spiderling silks(1 per attempt to make trueshot). go to ranger guild talk to who you guessed the person named trueshot. say &quot;I will 